  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-2c309fdc-7fff-803b-cf61-1ac88830b29a&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;The proposed development, by reason of its inappropriate design, materials, scale, and appearance, would result in an incongruous, overly prominent and discordant addition that would fail to preserve or enhance the character and appearance of the site and wider Broadway Market Conservation Area, contrary to Policies D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design led approach), HC1 (Heritage Conservation and Growth) of the London Plan (2021), Policies LP1 (High Quality Design), LP3 (Designated Heritage Assets) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and the Hackney Shopfront Design Guide SPG&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-e9cba997-7fff-3140-af9e-132b09dd5347&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;The proposed development, by reason of its inappropriate scale, form and location, would result in an unacceptable narrowing of the public footpath in a busy prominent location, which would detrimentally impact pedestrian movement, public realm accessibility and create conflicts between different users.The works would therefore negatively affect the quality and usability of the public realm and safety of pedestrians, contrary to Policies D8 (Public Realm), T5 (Cycling) of the London Plan (2021), Policies LP1 (High Quality Design), PP1 (Public Realm), LP41 (Liveable Neighbourhoods), LP42 (Walking and Cycling) and LP43 (Transport and Development) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
